create_function is not equivalent to a python lambda. It's just a function for creating other functions.<p>The key thing with a lambda in python is that it is defined at the usage site.<p>so you can do:<p><pre><code>    filter(lambda x: x > 42, mylist)
</code></pre>
Whereas in php that would be:<p><pre><code>    $mylambda = create_function('$x','return $x > 42;');
    filter($mylambda, $mylist);
</code></pre>
Yes, the usage  strings as code adds yet another level of WTF to this example.
